$0.23 EPS Expected for Caesars Entertainment Corp (CZR)


					

						July 27, 2017 - By test


Investors sentiment increased to 1.38 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.23, from 1.15 in 2016Q3. It is positive, as 17 investors sold Caesars Entertainment Corp shares while 25 reduced holdings. 23 funds opened positions while 35 raised stakes. 94.32 million shares or 1.05% more from 93.34 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported.
 62,309 were accumulated by Highbridge Capital Mgmt Ltd Limited Liability Company. Starwood Capital Grp Management Ltd Liability accumulated 5.8% or 2.42 million shares. 1.37M are owned by Group Holdg Ag. Great West Life Assurance Can reported 0% of its portfolio in Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR). Pdts Prns Ltd Company has invested 0.08% in Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR). Sg Americas Ltd Liability invested 0% in Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR). Strs Ohio owns 80,500 shares or 0% of their US portfolio. 77,479 were accumulated by Ahl Prtn Llp. Invesco Ltd holds 0% or 68,922 shares in its portfolio. Price T Rowe Associates Md stated it has 78,176 shares or 0% of all its holdings. Voya Invest Mngmt Ltd Liability Co owns 22,467 shares for 0% of their portfolio. Parametric Assocs Limited Company reported 0% in Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR). The New York-based Long Pond L P has invested 1.13% in Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR). Pentwater Cap Mngmt Lp holds 379,516 shares. National Bank & Trust Of Nova Scotia reported 0.02% in Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR).
 Analysts expect Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR) to report $0.23 EPS on August, 1.They anticipate $14.48 EPS change or 101.61 % from last quarter’s $-14.25 EPS. CZR’s profit would be $34.14 million giving it 13.91 P/E if the $0.23 EPS is correct. After having $-3.71 EPS previously, Caesars Entertainment Corp’s analysts see -106.20 % EPS growth. The stock decreased 0.39% or $0.05 during the last trading session, reaching $12.8. About 2.68M shares traded or 42.55% up from the average. Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR) has risen 62.44% since July 27, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 45.74% the S&P500.






Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR) Ratings Coverage
Among 2 analysts covering Caesars Entertainment (NASDAQ:CZR), 1 have Buy rating, 1 Sell and 0 Hold. Therefore 50% are positive. Caesars Entertainment had 3 analyst reports since December 14, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm has “Buy” rating by Oppenheimer given on Tuesday, June 6. The firm earned “Underweight” rating on Monday, December 14 by Barclays Capital. On Wednesday, May 31 the stock rating was initiated by Oppenheimer with “Buy”.
Caesars Entertainment Corporation is a holding company. The company has market cap of $1.90 billion. The Firm provides casino-entertainment and hospitality services. It currently has negative earnings. The Company’s divisions include Caesars Entertainment Resort Properties, LLC , Caesars Growth Partners, LLC (CGP) and Other.
More notable recent Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR) news were published by: Prnewswire.com which released: “Caesars Entertainment Appoints Senior Executives to Lead New Growth Initiatives” on July 06, 2017, also Gurufocus.com with their article: “Caesars Entertainment Corporation to Report 2017 Second-Quarter Results on …” published on July 20, 2017, Nasdaq.com published: “Commit To Purchase Caesars Entertainment Corp At $7, Earn 7.9% Using Options” on June 27, 2017. More interesting news about Caesars Entertainment Corp (NASDAQ:CZR) were released by: Seekingalpha.com and their article: “Hail Caesar! Is Caesars Entertainment Corporation A Good Buy?” published on June 28, 2017 as well as Reviewjournal.com‘s news article titled: “Caesars shareholders take new steps to emerge from bankruptcy” with publication date: July 25, 2017.


